---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Love Your Family — Digital Detox Tool Stack"
  description="The three-tool digital detox stack for families: Firewalla Gold Plus for home Wi-Fi control, Freedom for cross-platform coverage, and ScreenTime for cellular-level limits."
  canonicalPath="/love-your-family/takeaways-digital-detox/"
>
  <a class="overlay-back" href="/love-your-family/takeaways/">&#8592; Back to Takeaways</a>
  <a class="overlay-close" href="/" aria-label="Close">&times;</a>

  <div class="takeaways-content">
    <span class="takeaways-tag">Love Your Family</span>
    <h1 class="takeaways-title">Digital Detox: The Three-Tool Stack</h1>
    <p style="font-family:'EB Garamond',serif;font-size:.95rem;color:#7A7368;font-style:italic;margin-bottom:2.5rem">No single tool closes every gap. Here's how the three work together.</p>

    <div class="dd-topic-list">
      <a class="dd-topic-link" href="#dd-firewalla">Firewalla Gold Plus — Home Wi-Fi</a>
      <a class="dd-topic-link" href="#dd-freedom">Freedom — Cross-Platform Devices</a>
      <a class="dd-topic-link" href="#dd-screentime">ScreenTime — Cellular Coverage</a>
      <a class="dd-topic-link" href="#dd-stack">How the Stack Works Together</a>
    </div>

    <div class="dd-category" id="dd-firewalla">
      <div class="detox-tool-header">
        <div class="detox-tool-label">Tool 01</div>
        <div class="detox-tool-name">Firewalla Gold Plus</div>
        <div class="detox-tool-tagline">Home Wi-Fi Only</div>
      </div>

      <div class="detox-tool-body">
        <div class="detox-capability-label">What It Can Do</div>
        <div class="dd-item">Set digital boundaries and time limits for the entire family from a single dashboard</div>
        <div class="dd-item">Block all devices on the network at once — ideal for dinner time, bedtime, or family moments that deserve full attention</div>
        <div class="dd-item">Filter out all porn, violence, and malware at the network level before it ever reaches a screen in your home</div>
        <div class="dd-item">Enforce safe search across all devices automatically, with no per-device configuration needed</div>
        <div class="dd-item">Restrict TV time across streaming apps like Netflix and Hulu for specific devices or groups of devices</div>

        <div class="detox-blindspot-label">Blind Spots</div>
        <div class="detox-blindspot-item">Completely useless the moment anyone leaves the house — coverage ends at your router</div>
        <div class="detox-blindspot-item">An iPhone can bypass all restrictions instantly by switching to cellular data</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="dd-category" id="dd-freedom">
      <div class="detox-tool-header">
        <div class="detox-tool-label">Tool 02</div>
        <div class="detox-tool-name">Freedom</div>
        <div class="detox-tool-tagline">Cross-Platform Computer Coverage</div>
      </div>

      <div class="detox-tool-body">
        <div class="detox-capability-label">What It Can Do</div>
        <div class="dd-item">Schedule and sync blocks across phones and computers simultaneously — one session covers every device</div>
        <div class="dd-item">Restrict access to unwanted websites and apps no matter what Wi-Fi network you're connected to</div>
        <div class="dd-item">Create recurring block sessions to enforce healthy separation between work time and personal time</div>
        <div class="dd-item">Activate Locked Mode so you cannot quit an active session even if you delete the app — accountability built in</div>

        <div class="detox-blindspot-label">Blind Spots</div>
        <div class="detox-blindspot-item">No smart TV blocking — streaming devices on the living room television are outside its reach</div>
        <div class="detox-blindspot-item">Technically deletable when Locked Mode is not active — requires intentional discipline to use consistently</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="dd-category" id="dd-screentime">
      <div class="detox-tool-header">
        <div class="detox-tool-label">Tool 03</div>
        <div class="detox-tool-name">ScreenTime</div>
        <div class="detox-tool-tagline">Cellular Coverage</div>
      </div>

      <div class="detox-tool-body">
        <div class="detox-capability-label">What It Can Do</div>
        <div class="dd-item">Set digital boundaries and time limits on your own device even when away from home — cellular and Wi-Fi both covered</div>
        <div class="dd-item">Give someone else in the house the passcode so they can keep you accountable — removes the ability to self-bypass</div>
        <div class="dd-item">Schedule Downtime windows that cannot be bypassed even with a full factory reset of the device</div>
        <div class="dd-item">Group apps together by category — social media, games, entertainment — and set a combined daily time limit for the whole group</div>

        <div class="detox-blindspot-label">Blind Spots</div>
        <div class="detox-blindspot-item">iPhone only — Android users have no equivalent with the same depth of enforcement</div>
        <div class="detox-blindspot-item">Zero coverage on any computer, laptop, or desktop machine</div>
        <div class="detox-blindspot-item">No network-level filtering — can't block content for other family members on the same network</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="tk-section" id="dd-stack">
      <div class="tk-section-title">How the Three Work Together</div>
      <p style="font-family:'EB Garamond',serif;font-size:.95rem;color:#5E554B;line-height:1.8;margin-bottom:1.25rem">Each tool covers a different layer — and together they leave almost no escape hatch. Firewalla owns the home: every device on your Wi-Fi is filtered and time-limited at the network level, with zero configuration needed on individual screens. The moment someone walks out the door, Freedom takes over: it syncs blocks across all personal devices regardless of which network they're on, and Locked Mode ensures a moment of weakness can't undo hours of discipline. ScreenTime fills the last gap — it enforces limits at the cellular level on the iPhone itself, meaning even switching off Wi-Fi entirely doesn't break the guardrails. The result is overlapping coverage that turns environmental design into your greatest asset. You're no longer relying on willpower to fight a billion-dollar attention economy. You've built a system that works even when your motivation doesn't.</p>

      <div class="tk-grid">
        <div class="tk-card">
          <div class="tk-card-title">At Home</div>
          <p>Firewalla handles the whole household. Dinner time, bedtime, and family moments protected at the router — no per-device setup required.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="tk-card">
          <div class="tk-card-title">On the Road</div>
          <p>Freedom syncs across all personal devices. Work blocks, social media limits, and Locked Mode follow you wherever you go.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="tk-card">
          <div class="tk-card-title">On the Phone</div>
          <p>ScreenTime enforces limits at the cellular level — even with Wi-Fi off and the Freedom app deleted, Downtime still holds.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  html { scroll-behavior: smooth; }

  .detox-tool-header {
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }

  .detox-tool-label {
    font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.58rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.22em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #b79c5c;
    margin-bottom: 0.3rem;
  }

  .detox-tool-name {
    font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif;
    font-size: 1.45rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: #4f4a44;
    line-height: 1.2;
    margin-bottom: 0.2rem;
  }

  .detox-tool-tagline {
    font-family: 'EB Garamond', serif;
    font-size: 0.92rem;
    font-style: italic;
    color: #9e8c78;
  }

  .detox-tool-body {
    padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
    background: rgba(70, 61, 52, 0.02);
    border: 1px solid rgba(199, 187, 170, 0.35);
    border-radius: 4px;
  }

  .detox-capability-label {
    font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.58rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #6a6156;
    margin-bottom: 0.6rem;
  }

  .detox-blindspot-label {
    font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.58rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #a07c6a;
    margin-top: 1.4rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.6rem;
  }

  .detox-blindspot-item {
    font-family: 'EB Garamond', serif;
    font-size: 0.92rem;
    color: #7a6e66;
    line-height: 1.75;
    padding: 0.55rem 0 0.55rem 1.2rem;
    border-left: 2px solid rgba(160, 124, 106, 0.2);
    margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
    font-style: italic;
  }
</style>
